    "date": "2020-06-11T18:03:50Z",
    "text": "Corporate Accountability Act\n\nThis bill requires corporations that receive federal aid related to COVID-19 (i.e., coronavirus disease 2019) to (1) provide at least 14 days of fully paid leave to all workers, (2) pay each employee a wage of not less than $15 an hour, and (3) limit CEO and executive pay."
